进来坐下吧。

191
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,600
You wanted to see me?
一切都还好吗？

192
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,740
Yes, Anthony.
你看起来有点心事重重。

193
00:07:35,740 --> 00:07:40,200
Come on in and have a seat.
嗯，Anthony，这不会是一次轻松的谈话。

194
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:41,440
Is everything okay?
公司做出了一些决定，这些决定将直接影响你的工作。

195
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:43,560
You seem a bit preoccupied.
好吧。

196
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:48,440
Well, Anthony, this is not going to be an easy conversation.
我不想拐弯抹角，所以我就直说了。

197
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:53,640
The company has made some decisions which will have a direct impact on your employment.
我们得让你走了。

198
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,280
Okay.
什么？

199
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:58,920
I don't want to beat around the bush, so I'm just going to come out with it.
为什么？

200
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:00,520
We're going to have to let you go.
我是说，就这样？

201
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,520
What?
什么？

202
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,520
Why?
为什么？

203
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:04,360
I mean, just like that?
我是说，就这样？

204
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,360
I'm fired?
我被解雇了？

205
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:09,960
I'm sorry, but to be honest, you're a terrible employee.
抱歉，但说实话，你是个糟糕的员工。

206
00:08:09,960 --> 00:08:11,200
What?
什么？

207
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,760
I resent that.
我对此感到不满。

208
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:17,360
Anthony, you were caught making international calls from the office phone.
安东尼，你被抓到用办公室电话打国际长途。

209
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:24,280
You called in sick eight times this month and you smell like alcohol.
你这个月请了八次病假，而且身上还有酒味。

210
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:29,600
So, Erica, have you ever fired anyone?
那么，埃里卡，你解雇过别人吗？

211
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,240
I have fired a lot of people.
我解雇过很多人。

212
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,240
Wow.
哇。

213
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,920
You are a mean person.
你是个刻薄的人。

214
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:34,920
Oh, yeah.
哦，是啊。

215
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:41,000
Well, you know, there are some people who really do silly things like come to work drunk.
嗯，你知道，有些人确实会做傻事，比如喝醉了来上班。

216
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:44,240
And if you do that, you're obviously going to get fired.
如果你那样做，显然会被解雇。

217
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:48,600
But in the United States, actually, there is an interesting way of firing people.
但在美国，实际上有一种有趣的解雇方式。

218
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:50,400
They get a pink slip.
他们会收到一张粉红单。

219
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,960
Oh, yeah.
哦，是啊。

220
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:55,440
But I guess this is just a little bit different than getting fired.
但我想这和直接被解雇有点不同。

221
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:58,880
You get a pink slip when you get laid off.
当你被裁员时会收到粉红单。

222
00:08:58,880 --> 00:08:59,880
Right.
对。

223
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:03,520
I mean, if you come to work drunk, you get fired immediately, right?
我是说，如果你喝醉了来上班，你会立刻被解雇，对吧？

224
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:07,640
But when you get a pink slip, so it's basically a little pink paper that tells you that you
但当你收到粉红单时，它基本上是一张粉红色的小纸条，告诉你

225
00:09:07,640 --> 00:09:08,840
have been laid off.
你被裁员了。

226
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,840
Yeah.
嗯。

227
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,960
And so when you hear somebody say we sent out.
所以当你听到有人说我们发出了……

228
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:13,960
Yeah.
嗯。

229
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:18,720
So when you hear somebody talk about pink slips, like we send like our company sent
所以当你听到有人谈论粉红单，比如我们公司发出了

230
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:25,200
out 500 pink slips, you know, that means that 500 people got laid off or I got a pink slip
500张粉红单，你知道，那意味着500人被裁员了，或者我今天收到了一张粉红单

231
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,200
today.
今天。

232
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,200
That means you got laid off.
那意味着你被裁员了。

233
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,200
Right.
对。

234
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,200
Yeah.
嗯。

235
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,840
That's actually interesting because I don't know any other country that actually has this
这其实挺有意思的，因为我不知道还有哪个国家有这种

236
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:34,760
of special color, special color for firing people.
特殊的颜色，专门用来解雇人。

237
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:35,760
Yeah.
嗯。

238
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,760
How about in your country?
你们国家呢？

239
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:40,120
Is there a special color for pink slips?
有特殊的颜色代表粉红单吗？

240
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:45,560
If you guys have any stories as well, maybe about being fired or maybe you've had to fire
如果你们也有故事，也许关于被解雇，或者你不得不解雇

241
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:46,560
somebody.
别人。

242
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:48,640
Come to our website and tell us about it.
来我们的网站告诉我们吧。

243
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:49,640
Right.
对。

244
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,640
EnglishPod.com.
EnglishPod.com。

245
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:51,840
There you can leave your questions and comments.
在那里你可以留下你的问题和评论。

246
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:56,440
Erika and I are always there trying to answer your questions and also our great community
埃里卡和我总是在那里努力回答你们的问题，还有我们很棒的社区

247
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,440
is there.
也在那里。

248
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:58,440
They will also help.
他们也会帮忙。

249
00:09:58,440 --> 00:09:59,440
Okay, guys.
好了，各位。

250
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,440
Well, we're out of time for today.
嗯，我们今天的时间到了。

251
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:01,440
But until next time.
但下次再见。

252
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,440
Bye.
再见。

253
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:31,440
Bye.
再见。
